        <h1>About us</h1>
        <p>
The Gift of Time is a non-profit organization with the goal of promoting volunteering at both the micro-community and macro-global level.  It’s a simple concept, people commonly donate money on behalf of others – why can’t we donate time?  The answer is we can but we don’t.  We are missing a platform to productize our time in the form of a gift. Charities offer certification of a gift and a registry for all donations; this is the core service offering of the Gift of Time.  Secondary to making this gift possible, we want to maximize the impact and emotional influence this gift can have.  Therefore, we leverage three attributes of a perfect gift:<br>
<ul>
<li>Highly personalized</li>
<li>High value by donating personal resources</li>
<li>Proof of planning, effort and time spent</li>
</ul>
<br>
There is no project too small and no idea too unique or personal for the Gift of Time.  We ask that our users dig deep, act selflessly and come up with an idea that the recipient will feel very strongly about.  The more personalized it is, the greater the impact.  Furthermore, the gift can be one hour, day or week of volunteering.  Alternatively, it can be a short time for a longer duration, a few hours a week for a few months.  You know how valuable your time is – make the decision that works best for you.  Lastly, plan out your gift; whether there’s a specific event or you’re being entrepreneurial in creating something on your own, proper planning will maximize your impact.
Tyler Sharpe, a graduate of the Richard Ivey School of Business, came up with the idea in high school, developed the business model and presented it with his peers in a university business competition under the category “what do you get for the person that has everything?”  A finalist in the competition, Tyler has wanted to turn this idea into a reality for some time.  With the help of past colleagues and dear friends, Steve Long [website development] and Matthew Rabson [strategy and market outreach], the Gift of Time is now live and operational.
   
        </p>
